Capturing and incorporating operational pain points
Closing the loop post-incident
0.3.5 Ops-Safe Documentation Standards
Writing for on-call readability
Playbook-style clarity
0.4 Failure Ownership Principle
0.4.1 Redefining Failure
Functional success vs operational failure
Silent failures and delayed impact
0.4.2 Failure Anticipation
Identifying likely failure modes
Designing for degradation and fallback
0.4.3 Failure Traceability
Linking failures back to requirements
Post-incident requirement audits
0.4.4 Failure Communication
Transparent reporting during incidents
Avoiding blame-shifting language
0.4.5 Continuous Improvement Through Failure
Turning incidents into requirement improvements
Institutionalizing lessons learned
0.5 Section Exit Criteria (Pass / Fail)
A BA passes Section 0 if:
Ops trusts their documents
Ambiguity is proactively eliminated
Incidents don’t reveal requirement gaps
Accountability is visible, not claimed
Fail here → no progression to Section 1.

